snippet.textDisplay:
No one seems to be comparing the trajectory of Meghan to that of Camilla, who was widely criticized for an adulturous relationship with Prince Charles but because of her subsequent behavior and further acquantence with her personality, won over the British public as well as other members of the royal family. Despite the bad press she received, Camilla persevered due to her commitment to her now husband. She was loyal and committed. Meghan on the other hand received wide adulation and was welcomed in Harry's family from the beginning. Seemingly she couldn't tolerate the fact that the press was not totally complimentary and succeeded in alienating Harry from his brother based on her contention that she was not treated well by the royal family. How she could say that I don't know. Her family's disgraceful behavior was forgiven, she was accepted despite being divorced and having widely publicized erotic pictures in the public domain. She was able to break many taboos or customs that other royal women abide by and acted as almost a free agent within the philantrophic sphere. So in my view she has little to complain about, but persisted in being bitter and alledging that she was rejected because of racial prejudice. Her departure from the royal family, taking Harry with her, is a confirmation of the original reservations about Harry marrying someone who was American, who if she got divorced might take any children with her and depart
England, and had undergone a rather brief courtship by royal customs. Other royals tending to marry after periods of almost 10 years acquaintance.

snippet.textDisplay: I am British and live in the UK.  I was pleased to see that Harry and Megan were able to marry, give the Queen her due she has tried hard to keep the Royal Family current.  I was very disturbed and disappointed however, at how the popular press treated her, it seemed to pander to the lowest common denominator but not necessarily to the majority of the British public.  It saddened me that, to protect his wife and their child, Prince Harry felt he had to leave the country but I don’t blame him. They are his No 1 responsibilities, he more than anyone else knows how the press can negatively impact on his family.  He did not sign up for the attention his family gets, he was born into it and although his station brings great wealth and position there are more important things.  If a king can abdicate his responsibility I see no reason why a prince cannot elect to do the same thing, especially when he has such overwhelming reasons to do so.  The obnoxious women who commented so negatively about Megan is a member of a small group of elitists who believe themselves to be the arbiters of what the Royal family should and should not do.  They are like pilot fish who survive and make themselves seem important on detritus, with no real knowledge of the pressures and conflicts that affects their hosts.  Shame on them.
